I made a guitar out of plastic trash by shredding bottles caps, milk jugs and old buckets and then melting them in an oven. I made the guitar for Fiverr and they are giving it away. to enter, please do the following:

Follow me  and @Fiverr
Tag three friends on Fiverr’s post
Comment your favorite band on Fiverr’s post

 Fiverr will announce the winner on their Instagram page Friday, the 29th at 2pm EST. Participants will have until then to enter. Shout out to @alexxmedia for inventing the turn your phone intro. #sponsored #ad #makersgonnamake #recycle #designdunker #guitar

node.text: Solar landscaping lights are inexpensive and easy to modify into all sorts of applications. I turned this nose cone from a wind turbine into large pendant light. This is part of the patio makeover series we did that was sponsored by @krylonbrand This Krylon Fusion All-In-One spray paint is great on so many different surfaces and has 5x greater adhesion. We used it on fiberglass, plastic, wood, steel, and aluminum to transform junk into furniture. The full series is up on the homemade modern channel. Shout out to krylon for supporting creative up cycling! #ad #sponsored

node.text:
I became interested in sustainability not because I had lofty aspirations about saving the world but as grounded way to tie a collective purpose to my individual ideas. 
I started making a YouTube videos as way to share these ideas, and by building my designs with my own two I hands I really get to understand the consequences of these ideas and take ownership of the process. 
 
Being hands on has really made me appreciate the value of great tools.  From massive cranes and trucks to move windmill blades and shipping containers to the memory cards in the cameras - tools allow me to transform an idea into physical reality and then share the results digitally with millions of people. 
 
I am trying to make my designs sustainable and celebrate the small victories without dwelling on the multitude of compromises I inevitably make. I try to remember that I am just one of 7 billion people, but I think it would be so cool to know that you did more than your share. That your impact was greater than your footprint. 
 
As a creative, of course I want my work to stand out, but as a global citizen I want to stand with - not apart. 
I understand that a collective challenge this great and complex won’t be solved by the perfection of few, but rather by the incremental progress of many.
 
Branded content about sustainability can be pretty cringey at times. An awareness of the marketplace motivations and the pressure to perform economically justifies the cynicism, but I am grateful for effort and imperfect progress. I have been pursuing, not achieving, sustainable design for almost 20 years and while we are still a long way away, progress has been made. I am grateful for this collaboration with @samsungmemory This type of support was unimaginable when I started this journey and it makes me optimistic about the where we will be in the next 20 years. 
 
#SamsungMemory #SaveAlltheProgress #Ad #sustainability

node.text: Building the shipping container house was so much fun. I enjoyed my time in architecture but full ownership of project from finding the land, sketching out the initial design, figuring out how to get it permitted, renting the cranes, and welding the steel was thrilling. It’s was a small architecture project but a huge design adventure and I learned so much by having to build the things I drew. That being said cutting and welding steel in 105 degree Joshua tree weather is not the most comfortable way to spend a summer. There is a video series documenting the entire process on The Modern Home Project YouTube channel and I recently started a couple of new container projects with my business partner @adamwini I want to compare the cost of custom site building to pre-fab construction so we acquired some more land and are in the permitting process now. For these new projects we are working with an all star team of container design of @radlabsd and @steelblox Photos by @calebkuhl #shippingcontainerhome #shippingcontainer #shippingcontainerhouse #containerhomes #containerhouse #containerarchitecture #architecture #tinyhouse #moderndesign #joshuatreehouse

node.text: Designing something from scratch can seem a bit daunting at times. With a blank canvas every first move can seem so willful and arbitrary. For sure there are times when I have a clear vision and know exactly what what I want to create but when that is not the case I like to find something that has been discarded and deemed no longer useful and see what I can do with it. It takes the pressure of perfection off and make it a low stakes game of improvisation and improvement. I can relax and let the lessons I learned from past projects help solve small technical problems free from the self imposed challenge of definitive personal expression. These projects are side quests or design vacations where i can feel productive, active and useful. Shout out to @krylonbrand for sponsoring this series on up cycling. We turned this old satellite dish into a swinging lounge and furnished our patio with junk collected from @ijessup house. All of the videos in the series are now live on homemade modern.  #upcycle #upcycledfurniture #upcyclingfurniture #recycle #sustainability #sustainabledesign

I used @quikreteconcrete countertop mix in white, added some @limestrong pigment in sage, as well as a layer of @totalboat thick set epoxy resin. I love doing these small experiments because they unlock so many ideas for bigger projects. The full video is up on the homemade modern channel. Shout out to @replicasurfaces for sponsoring this project and hooking me up with a mobile photo studio!

node.text: Fiber reinforced cement is one of the most cost effective DIY materials I can think of and it doesn’t require power tools to work with. With a single bag of @quikreteconcrete QUIKWALL surface bonding cement I made landscape boulders, hanging planters, and a house for Gary the squirrel. Check out the homemade modern channel for a bunch of videos using quikwall for all sorts of diy projects. #concrete #pottery #handmade #diyproject #cement #plaster

node.text: Ok so building a house for Gary the 🐿 is kind of silly but I have been experimenting with surface bonding cement which is a cement plaster with fiber reinforcement already mixed in. It’s incredibly strong and is one of the most versatile and inexpensive DIY materials I have used. For Gary’s house I tested out joint compound as a finishing plaster on top of the cement plaster and it worked great as a combination. For surface bonding cement I used Quikwall by @quikreteconcrete and did a series of experiments for a video which is now live on homemade modern. #squirrelsofinstagram #chipmonks #snacks
